<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-419-894  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 419 894.andM;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Government Computer News  April 30 1990 v9 n9 p45(2)* Full Text COPYRIGHT Ziff-Davis Publishing Co. 1990.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Legent's new SQL-driven tool can do what people used to do.andO;(Structured Query Language Version 3.0 of AutoMate/MVS) (productannouncement)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Schwartz, Karen D.andM;</AUTHOR><DESCRIPT>Company:   LEGENT Corp. (product introduction).andO;Product:   Automate/MVS 3.0 (Data center management software) (productintroduction).andO;Topic:     Product IntroductionStructured Query LanguageRelational DBMSMainframe Computers.andO;Feature:   illustrationchart.andO;Caption:   (The AutoMate system). (chart)andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>Legent's New SQL-Driven Tool Can Do What People Used to DoandM;Legent Corp. has released a Structured Query Language Version 3.0 ofAutoMate/MVS, its automated operations too for IBM-type mainframes.andM;The new version includes the relational data framework, an SQL-driven systemthat lets data center managers manipulate critical operations data throughthe use of data tables, and the system state manager, which automaticallymonitors and manages a system's state.andM;About 20 federal sites use AutoMate in the Army, the Agriculture Department,the Air Force, the Securities Exchange Commission and the House ofRepresentatives, said Ed Colbert, manager for federal programs for theVienna, Va., company.andP;  AutoMate, written in assembly language, is a softwaretool that replaces many of th e functions previously performed by humancomputer operators, said Robert Clarke, an account manager at Legent.andM;Because the government today has less money to spend on computer services, ithas become increasingly important to replace human functions with advancedtechnology, Clarke said.andP;  The goal is for nobody to monitor the consoles, hesaid.andM;With hundreds of programs running simultaneously, it becomes difficult toknow the right answer and format to fix a specific problem, Clarke said.andM;All error messages for all programs can be programmed into AutoMate so thateach program's specific error codes are customized into the sytem.andM;A new feature of Version 3.0 is its relational data framework, which allowsstorage and access of data in a two-dimensional table that containsinformation about a particular computer site.andM;The table can consist of a list of people to be notified when a criticalproblem arises.andP;  AutoMate automatically will dial the specified people when aproblem occurs, prompt them for their passwords and tell them over thetelephone about the problem.andM;The system also can include a voice card, Clarke said, and can present theproblem solver with options over the telephone.andP;  The problem solver then canhit the appropriate option on his telephone keypad to execute the action.andM;The relational data framework also can store a list of procedures to be usedwhen a system has problems, Clarke said.andP;  If an agency with multiplelocations has a problem with computers at one site, the processing can bepicked up at another.andM;AutoMate is available now for operating systems other than MVS, Clarke said.andO;Release 3.0 also is available in AutoMate/VM, allowing the system to run onsmaller IBM-compatible machines, and in AutoMage/XC, which works withmachines from Digital Equipment Corp., Data General Corp., Wang LaboratoriesInc., Cray Research Inc., and others not compatible with the IBM structure.andM;Lease prices start at $10,000 per year.andO;</TEXT></DOC>